    <div class=header>
        <h2>What is a Storm</h2>
    </div>

    <div class=content>
        <p>A storm is a violent atmospheric disturbance characterized by strong winds,
            heavy rain, thunder, lightning, and sometimes hail or snow. Storms can be 
            caused by various meteorological factors such as low-pressure systems, 
            tropical cyclones, or cold fronts. These weather phenomena can travel across
             vast regions, causing significant damage to infrastructure and natural landscapes.
              The average wind speed in a storm can reach 70 mph, with some of the most 
              powerful storms, like hurricanes, producing winds exceeding 150 mph. One of 
              the most destructive storms on record was Hurricane Patricia in 2015, with 
              sustained winds of 215 mph. The term "storm" comes from the Old English word "storm," meaning "tempest" or "violent weather."</p>
    </div>

